target/
.git/
sidecar/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
reqres/
widget/
*.md

# `.env` alone was **root-anchored** — Docker matches patterns against the whole path relative to the
# context root, so it never covered `web/.env`. That file was being copied into the Rust builder
# layer on every image build. It does not reach the final api/worker images (those copy only the
# binaries out of the builder), but it sat in the build cache, and it is the file most likely to
# acquire a secret later.
.env
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# The web app builds from its own context (`web/Dockerfile`), so none of it belongs in the Rust
# builder. `web/node_modules` alone is hundreds of megabytes of `COPY .` this image never reads.
web/
